translated: Björnby, Per Harald, practicing physician, Falkenberg, b. 3/3/03 in Arboga. Married in 1932 to Ingeborg Östnäs. Children: Anita b. 1934, Per b. 1936. He graduated from high school in Västerås in 1922, received his medical degree from Uppsala in 1926, and became a licensed physician there in 1931. He served as an assistant in the pathology department in Uppsala in 1926, as a physician at Sätra brunn from 1926-1928, as a junior physician there from 1930-1932, as an assistant physician in the medical department of Akademiska sjukhuset in 1931, in the otolaryngology department the same year, and in the surgical department in 1932. He worked as a physician at Falkenbergs havsbad from 1933, at Falkenbergs epidemics hospital in 1934, as an interim city physician in Falkenberg from 1934-1935, as a practicing physician in Falkenberg from 1932, and as a school physician at Katrinebergs folkhögskola. He was also a member of the board of directors for Falkenbergs las.
